At least eight persons have died in a lone auto accident that occurred at Farin-Doki village along Minna-Suleja road in Paikoro Local Government Area of Niger State. It was gathered that the accident which occurred yesterday evening at about 7 pm involved a bus with a Kano registration number KMC 297 ZU conveying passengers from Katsina to Lagos. DAILY POST learnt that the driver, one Ilyasu Bala, lost control of the vehicle at a point around Farin-Doki village due to a reported mechanical fault. Eyewitness account stated that the driver, six others and a child lost their lives on the spot of the auto crash. The source explained that the injured victims were conveyed by some villagers in the area to the hospital at Gawu in Gurara Local Government Area of Niger State for medical attention. Confirming the incident, the state Police Public Relations Officer, PRO, DSP Wasiu Abiodun, said the lone accident was due to a reported mechanical fault developed by the vehicle during the journey that caused it to somersault. “Unfortunately, the bus somersaulted while the driver, one Ilyasu Bala and six others died on the spot, eight other passengers sustained various degrees of injuries,” the police image maker disclosed. However, he explained that the Police patrol team attached to Paiko Division quickly moved to the scene and rushed the injured victims to the nearest hospital for medical attention, while the corpses were taken to IBB Hospital Morgue.